      • addJarDirectory

        public void addJarDirectory(java.lang.String directoryUrl,
                            boolean recursively)
        Description copied from interface: VirtualFilePointerContainer
        Adds directory as a root of jar files. After this call the VirtualFilePointerContainer.getFiles() will additionally return jar files in this directory (and, if recursively was set, the jar files in all-subdirectories). VirtualFilePointerContainer.getUrls() will additionally return the directoryUrl.
        Specified by:
        addJarDirectory in interface VirtualFilePointerContainer

      • removeJarDirectory

        public boolean removeJarDirectory(java.lang.String directoryUrl)
        Description copied from interface: VirtualFilePointerContainer
        Removes directory from the roots of jar files. After that the VirtualFilePointerContainer.getFiles() and VirtualFilePointerContainer.getUrls() etc will not return jar files in this directory anymore.
        Specified by:
        removeJarDirectory in interface VirtualFilePointerContainer
        Returns:
        true if removed
